settings.description: the end of the line is now here. one final half of Bowser's newest castle awaits, and it's filled to the brim with bros! think you can take down the king in this dangerous trek?
just like how the real e-reader levels have a two part special that's all about one tough as nails challenge.. instead of an airship, you get a huge castle! watch out, The Big Boo awaits you!
watch out! you're in the middle of a warzone with all these dangerous cannons and Bob-ombs being fired out! think you can find the hidden mad lad as well?
Honestly loosely based on one level from the SMBX game 'the invasion 2', for remember a level with the hammer bros themes and mario bros elements? well... here I'm trying to go for that theme!
semi-redo of a very old level perhaps. same theme, different layout ya know? though this time I went a bit overboard on them there tilting platforms instead!
Fun Fact: I'm terrible at making underwater levels, so I just decided to take out the water in the underwater, thus creating an... under level.
so many red hot piranha plants! clearly, this dungeon of pipes is out to just roast you, so stay on your toes and don't get burned or biten!
what's up with all these spinning spiny shells? well... be glad ya aren't playing the NES and SNES version here, for ya can't stomp them in them versions of SMB3, but here? you can!
Thwomps and Thwimps! this place is full to the brim with these mad rocky foes! think you can make it out of these ruins without getting crushed?
strange spinning spheres with arrows on them! hop on top of such, and go for a ride! think you can use them to your advantage for getting through this cave?
watch out! this airship's full of plants! odd choice, but maybe the fire they spit is rather effective at keeping plumbers out!
watch out! boomerang bros are known to guard precious treasure in this long not so dangerous bridge!
Sometimes you have to wonder... where DO all these jumping and fire breathing statues come from? well... here's the answer.
Ice, munchers, flurries, penguins, and... shoes?! seems like this wild combo is something that's a bit toooo chill to exist, but it does!
Actually it's not too much of a panic, for this level's not tooooo difficult for one! yeah, good ol Chuck might try to get in your way, but that's all for the dangers here!
a whole castle filled with bricks that can be turned into koopas and mushrooms? what a dream! course, Bowser's waiting at the end to ruin the fun!
with a boatload of bullets! honestly love how the four way bullet bill generators exist, for they're such an underused feature found originally in super mario world.
watch out above! due to screencrunch of the GBA, you might wanna be extra careful in jumping high in this piranha infested cavern of pipes!

so much sand, with so many coins found deep under such! think you can unearth enough for a nice three extra lives?
don't forget to check what's in the bricks as well!

who would've thought that such a strange combo would come to be! best to learn how to use them though, and swim swiftly about with such!
PS: I am bad at underwater levels.
seems this normal ol wooden plains level got flooded by something! best to watch out for the flopping fish, for they can still harm you!
watch out! while there may be some nice treasure at the end, you'll need to use some lavaproof beachballs to cross through this dangerous pipeline!
cannons, cannons, and more cannons are all about what this airship is! think you can deal with Larry and his tricks in the end?
waterfalls, koopas, ptooies, and a incredible view of a nice sunset! what more can you ask for minus a hidden hammer suit?~
Galoombas! Galoombas as far as the eye can see! where do they all come from, nobody knows!
Good lord am I bad at puzzles! although... hopefully the ones I made'll be good enough to make you think on where to go to find the exit?
Bullets everywhere, and they're all dangerous! either they'll turn back to try to hit you again, or just seek you down for the perfect shot!

Caves... filled with bats and moles! don't forget the iconic buzzy beetles as well!

shame there's no cave ceiling tiles though.
Careful, these creepy crawling beetles just love roaming around on all these wooden walkways! think you can find their hidden Tanooki suit though?
Wiggler ahoy! seems these caterpillars and butterflies are all around this chilly place!

no scenery in the main area sadly.
either way, think you can brave this giant fortress and stop Boom Boom? for this time he's got some help!
so many fire bros! well, it's not too many, but still! watch your step in this heated nighttime desert level!
Ya know, while fire snakes are meant to be reddish orange... they look really good with a cool blue, so... why not build a nice chilly sky level featuring them for one?~
Rattle me bones! the big boo's new fortress is filled with bones and boos! think you can find the special treasure and take down the boss?
Suppose it's time for an old washed up mario flash level maker to step foot into a new light... with a new honestly great level making program as well! hopefully this level's fun too!
